-- Indonesia Stock Movers: Astra Agro, Benakat Petroleum, XL Axiata
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-01-30T09:22:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/indonesia-stock-movers-benakat-petroleum-london-sumatra-medco.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite Index (JCI)  fell 1.8 percent to 3,915.16,
the biggest drop since Nov. 21.  Oil producers:  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC)  , the
nation’s biggest listed oil company, retreated 3.1 percent to
2,350 rupiah, the lowest since Dec. 15.  PT Benakat Petroleum
Energy (BIPI)   lost 2.1 percent to 235 rupiah. Crude futures
in  New York  dropped for a second day, losing as much as 0.9
percent to $98.71 a barrel.  Palm oil producers:  PT Astra Agro Lestari (AALI)  , the
nation’s biggest listed plantation company by market value, fell
2.1 percent to 21,100 rupiah.  PT Bakrie Sumatera Plantations (UNSP) 
 decreased 1.7 percent to 290 rupiah. Palm-oil futures
declined as much as 1.6 percent to 3,085 ringgit ($1,008) a
metric ton in  Kuala Lumpur .  PT XL Axiata (EXCL)  , a unit of Malaysia’s Axiata Group
Bhd., sank 5.8 percent to 4,500 rupiah, the biggest loss since
Oct. 28. CIMB Investment Bhd. lowered its share-price estimate
to 5,300 rupiah, citing the potential for a lower profit margin
in 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
